-- Russia Equity Movers: Gazprom, Norilsk Nickel, Globaltrans
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 2012-04-27T12:32:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/russia-equity-movers-gazprom-norilsk-nickel-globaltrans.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  advanced
1.3 percent to 1,466.06 by 4:08 p.m. in Moscow, its biggest gain
in more than a week.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX) jumped 2.3 percent to 167.87 rubles,
headed for its biggest increase this month. Russia’s natural gas
export monopoly posted fourth-quarter profit today that beat
analysts’ estimates.  Globaltrans Investment Plc (GLTR)   climbed the most since
Sept. 7, adding 9.2 percent to $19.25 in London trading. The
rail-freight operator acquired the railway unit of Russian
billionaire  Alisher Usmanov ’s iron-ore producer Metalloinvest.  OAO GMK  Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX) rallied for the first time
in five days, surging 2.1 percent to 5,192 rubles. Usmanov said
he’s boosting the stake he controls in the world’s largest
nickel producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Nicholson in Moscow at 
